{
  "texts": [
    "Our SciBERT-HSLN architecture has the following layers: Word Embedding: Input is a sequence of tokens (t i,1,..., t i,m) of sentence s i, while output is a sequence of contextual word embeddings (w i,1,..., w i,m).",
    "Sentence Encoding: Input (w i,1,..., w i,m) is transformed via a Bi-LSTM [38] into the hidden token representations (h i,1,..., h i,m) (h i,t ∈ R d h) which are enriched with contextual information within the sentence.",
    "Then, attention pooling [41,88] with r heads produces a sentence vector e i ∈ R rd u.",
    "An attention head produces a weighted average over the token representations of a sentence.",
    "Multiple heads enable to capture several semantics of a sentence."
  ]
}